Provisions of the Judiciary Act to the contrary notwithstanding, the court shall have exclusive original jurisdiction to hear and decide the following cases:

Criminal cases wherein the accused is under sixteen years of age at the time of the filing of the case and which, at present, are cognizable by courts of first instance, city courts and municipal courts, except cases involving violations of municipal ordinances of the City of Iriga and of the different municipalities of Camarines Sur;

Cases involving custody, guardianship, adoption, paternity and acknowledgment;

Annulment of marriages, relief from marital obligations, legal separation of spouses, and actions for support;

Proceedings brought under the provisions of Articles one hundred sixteen, one hundred seventeen, two hundred twenty-five, two hundred fifty-one, and three hundred thirty-two of the Civil Code;

Proceedings for declaration of absence and for change of name;

Actions involving separation of property and other property relations between spouses;

Proceedings affecting a dependent or neglected child as hereinafter defined or other cases concerning the exercise or deprivation of parental authority.
